# echo --upper

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=goal -->
## Goal
Echo argv with optional uppercasing.
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=inputs-outputs -->
## Inputs and outputs
- argv: positional args optionally preceded by `--upper`
- stdin: ignored
- stdout: argv joined by spaces, uppercased iff `--upper` is set, plus newline
- stderr: empty on success
- exit codes: 0 on success
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=errors -->
## Error taxonomy
N/A: no error paths in v0
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=fs -->
## File-system contract
N/A
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=concurrency -->
## Concurrency
N/A
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=perf -->
## Performance bounds
N/A
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=examples-accept -->
## Acceptance examples
1. argv=["hello"] -> stdout="hello\n"
2. argv=["--upper","hello"] -> stdout="HELLO\n"
3. argv=["hello","world"] -> stdout="hello world\n"
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=examples-refuse -->
## Refusing examples
1. argv=["--unknown"] -> exits non-zero
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->

<!-- k4k:owner=user begin id=out-of-scope -->
## Out of scope
- everything except echoing argv with optional uppercase
<!-- k4k:owner=user end -->
